{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"This is a guy named Bob McKim."},{"time":3000,"text":"He was a creativity researcher in the '60s and '70s,"},{"time":8000,"text":"and also led the Stanford Design Program."},{"time":11000,"text":"And in fact, my friend and IDEO founder, David Kelley,"},{"time":14000,"text":"who’s out there somewhere, studied under him at Stanford."},{"time":20000,"text":"And he liked to do an exercise with his students"},{"time":26000,"text":"where he got them to take a piece of paper"},{"time":31000,"text":"and draw the person who sat next to them, their neighbor,"},{"time":35000,"text":"very quickly, just as quickly as they could."}]},{"cues":[{"time":37000,"text":"And in fact, we’re going to do that exercise right now."},{"time":40000,"text":"You all have a piece of cardboard and a piece of paper."},{"time":43000,"text":"It’s actually got a bunch of circles on it."},{"time":44000,"text":"I need you to turn that piece of paper over;"},{"time":45000,"text":"you should find that it’s blank on the other side."},{"time":48000,"text":"And there should be a pencil."},{"time":51000,"text":"And I want you to pick somebody that’s seated next to you,"},{"time":55000,"text":"and when I say, go, you’ve got 30 seconds to draw your neighbor, OK?"},{"time":63000,"text":"So, everybody ready? OK. Off you go."},{"time":68000,"text":"You’ve got 30 seconds, you’d better be fast."},{"time":71000,"text":"Come on: those masterpieces ..."},{"time":84000,"text":"OK? Stop. All right, now."}]},{"cues":[{"time":87000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":89000,"text":"Yes, lot’s of laughter. Yeah, exactly."},{"time":92000,"text":"Lots of laughter, quite a bit of embarrassment."}]},{"cues":[{"time":95000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":96000,"text":"Am I hearing a few \"sorry’s\"? I think I’m hearing a few sorry’s."},{"time":101000,"text":"Yup, yup, I think I probably am."},{"time":103000,"text":"And that’s exactly what happens every time,"},{"time":107000,"text":"every time you do this with adults."},{"time":109000,"text":"McKim found this every time he did it with his students."},{"time":112000,"text":"He got exactly the same response: lots and lots of sorry’s."}]},{"cues":[{"time":116000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":117000,"text":"And he would point this out as evidence"},{"time":121000,"text":"that we fear the judgment of our peers,"},{"time":124000,"text":"and that we’re embarrassed about showing our ideas"},{"time":128000,"text":"to people we think of as our peers, to those around us."},{"time":132000,"text":"And this fear is what causes us"},{"time":136000,"text":"to be conservative in our thinking."},{"time":139000,"text":"So we might have a wild idea,"},{"time":141000,"text":"but we’re afraid to share it with anybody else."}]},{"cues":[{"time":144000,"text":"OK, so if you try the same exercise with kids,"},{"time":147000,"text":"they have no embarrassment at all."},{"time":150000,"text":"They just quite happily show their masterpiece"},{"time":152000,"text":"to whoever wants to look at it."},{"time":157000,"text":"But as they learn to become adults,"},{"time":160000,"text":"they become much more sensitive to the opinions of others,"},{"time":163000,"text":"and they lose that freedom and they do start to become embarrassed."},{"time":168000,"text":"And in studies of kids playing, it’s been shown"},{"time":171000,"text":"time after time that kids who feel secure,"},{"time":175000,"text":"who are in a kind of trusted environment --"},{"time":178000,"text":"they’re the ones that feel most free to play."}]},{"cues":[{"time":184000,"text":"And if you’re starting a design firm, let’s say,"},{"time":187000,"text":"then you probably also want to create"},{"time":191000,"text":"a place where people have the same kind of security."},{"time":194000,"text":"Where they have the same kind of security to take risks."},{"time":197000,"text":"Maybe have the same kind of security to play."}]},{"cues":[{"time":201000,"text":"Before founding IDEO, David said that what he wanted to do"},{"time":206000,"text":"was to form a company where all the employees are my best friends."},{"time":212000,"text":"Now, that wasn’t just self-indulgence."},{"time":215000,"text":"He knew that friendship is a short cut to play."},{"time":221000,"text":"And he knew that it gives us a sense of trust,"},{"time":226000,"text":"and it allows us then to take the kind of creative risks"},{"time":229000,"text":"that we need to take as designers."},{"time":232000,"text":"And so, that decision to work with his friends --"},{"time":236000,"text":"now he has 550 of them -- was what got IDEO started."}]},{"cues":[{"time":243000,"text":"And our studios, like, I think, many creative workplaces today,"},{"time":247000,"text":"are designed to help people feel relaxed:"},{"time":250000,"text":"familiar with their surroundings,"},{"time":253000,"text":"comfortable with the people that they’re working with."},{"time":257000,"text":"It takes more than decor, but I think we’ve all seen that"},{"time":260000,"text":"creative companies do often have symbols in the workplace"},{"time":265000,"text":"that remind people to be playful,"},{"time":268000,"text":"and that it’s a permissive environment."},{"time":271000,"text":"So, whether it’s this microbus meeting room"},{"time":273000,"text":"that we have in one our buildings at IDEO;"},{"time":275000,"text":"or at Pixar, where the animators work in wooden huts and decorated caves;"},{"time":281000,"text":"or at the Googleplex, where"},{"time":283000,"text":"it’s famous for its [beach] volleyball courts,"},{"time":284000,"text":"and even this massive dinosaur skeleton with pink flamingos on it."},{"time":288000,"text":"Don’t know the reason for the pink flamingos,"},{"time":290000,"text":"but anyway, they’re there in the garden."},{"time":292000,"text":"Or even in the Swiss office of Google,"},{"time":294000,"text":"which perhaps has the most wacky ideas of all."},{"time":296000,"text":"And my theory is, that’s so the Swiss can prove"},{"time":298000,"text":"to their Californian colleagues that they’re not boring."},{"time":301000,"text":"So they have the slide, and they even have a fireman’s pole."},{"time":304000,"text":"Don’t know what they do with that, but they have one."}]},{"cues":[{"time":305000,"text":"So all of these places have these symbols."},{"time":308000,"text":"Now, our big symbol at IDEO is actually"},{"time":311000,"text":"not so much the place, it’s a thing."},{"time":313000,"text":"And it’s actually something that we invented a few years ago,"},{"time":316000,"text":"or created a few years ago."},{"time":317000,"text":"It’s a toy; it’s called a \"finger blaster.\""},{"time":320000,"text":"And I forgot to bring one up with me."},{"time":322000,"text":"So if somebody can reach under the chair that’s next to them,"},{"time":325000,"text":"you’ll find something taped underneath it."},{"time":327000,"text":"That’s great. If you could pass it up. Thanks, David, I appreciate it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":330000,"text":"So this is a finger blaster, and you will find that every one of you"},{"time":334000,"text":"has got one taped under your chair."},{"time":337000,"text":"And I’m going to run a little experiment. Another little experiment."},{"time":341000,"text":"But before we start, I need just to put these on."},{"time":344000,"text":"Thank you. All right."},{"time":346000,"text":"Now, what I’m going to do is, I’m going to see how --"},{"time":349000,"text":"I can’t see out of these, OK."},{"time":350000,"text":"I’m going to see how many of you at the back of the room"},{"time":352000,"text":"can actually get those things onto the stage."},{"time":354000,"text":"So the way they work is, you know,"},{"time":356000,"text":"you just put your finger in the thing,"},{"time":359000,"text":"pull them back, and off you go."},{"time":362000,"text":"So, don’t look backwards. That’s my only recommendation here."},{"time":367000,"text":"I want to see how many of you can get these things on the stage."},{"time":369000,"text":"So come on! There we go, there we go. Thank you. Thank you. Oh."},{"time":372000,"text":"I have another idea. I wanted to -- there we go."}]},{"cues":[{"time":375000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":379000,"text":"There we go."}]},{"cues":[{"time":380000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":384000,"text":"Thank you, thank you, thank you."},{"time":385000,"text":"Not bad, not bad. No serious injuries so far."}]},{"cues":[{"time":389000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":393000,"text":"Well, they’re still coming in from the back there;"},{"time":398000,"text":"they’re still coming in."},{"time":399000,"text":"Some of you haven’t fired them yet."},{"time":400000,"text":"Can you not figure out how to do it, or something?"},{"time":402000,"text":"It’s not that hard. Most of your kids figure out how to do this"},{"time":405000,"text":"in the first 10 seconds, when they pick it up."},{"time":408000,"text":"All right. This is pretty good; this is pretty good."},{"time":410000,"text":"Okay, all right. Let’s -- I suppose we'd better..."},{"time":416000,"text":"I'd better clear these up out of the way;"},{"time":417000,"text":"otherwise, I’m going to trip over them."},{"time":419000,"text":"All right. So the rest of you can save them"},{"time":422000,"text":"for when I say something particularly boring,"},{"time":424000,"text":"and then you can fire at me."}]},{"cues":[{"time":425000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":427000,"text":"All right. I think I’m going to take these off now,"},{"time":428000,"text":"because I can’t see a damn thing when I’ve -- all right, OK."},{"time":432000,"text":"So, ah, that was fun."}]},{"cues":[{"time":436000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":438000,"text":"All right, good."}]},{"cues":[{"time":440000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":442000,"text":"So, OK, so why?"},{"time":444000,"text":"So we have the finger blasters. Other people have dinosaurs, you know."},{"time":447000,"text":"Why do we have them? Well, as I said,"},{"time":449000,"text":"we have them because we think maybe playfulness is important."},{"time":453000,"text":"But why is it important?"},{"time":455000,"text":"We use it in a pretty pragmatic way, to be honest."},{"time":458000,"text":"We think playfulness helps us get to better creative solutions."},{"time":463000,"text":"Helps us do our jobs better,"},{"time":465000,"text":"and helps us feel better when we do them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":467000,"text":"Now, an adult encountering a new situation --"},{"time":471000,"text":"when we encounter a new situation we have a tendency"},{"time":474000,"text":"to want to categorize it just as quickly as we can, you know."},{"time":477000,"text":"And there’s a reason for that: we want to settle on an answer."},{"time":483000,"text":"Life’s complicated; we want to figure out"},{"time":486000,"text":"what’s going on around us very quickly."},{"time":487000,"text":"I suspect, actually, that the evolutionary biologists"},{"time":489000,"text":"probably have lots of reasons [for] why we want"},{"time":491000,"text":"to categorize new things very, very quickly."},{"time":494000,"text":"One of them might be, you know,"},{"time":496000,"text":"when we see this funny stripy thing:"},{"time":497000,"text":"is that a tiger just about to jump out and kill us?"},{"time":500000,"text":"Or is it just some weird shadows on the tree?"},{"time":501000,"text":"We need to figure that out pretty fast."},{"time":503000,"text":"Well, at least, we did once."},{"time":504000,"text":"Most of us don’t need to anymore, I suppose."}]},{"cues":[{"time":506000,"text":"This is some aluminum foil, right? You use it in the kitchen."},{"time":508000,"text":"That’s what it is, isn’t it? Of course it is, of course it is."},{"time":511000,"text":"Well, not necessarily."}]},{"cues":[{"time":513000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":515000,"text":"Kids are more engaged with open possibilities."},{"time":518000,"text":"Now, they’ll certainly -- when they come across something new,"},{"time":520000,"text":"they’ll certainly ask, \"What is it?\""},{"time":522000,"text":"Of course they will. But they’ll also ask, \"What can I do with it?\""},{"time":525000,"text":"And you know, the more creative of them"},{"time":527000,"text":"might get to a really interesting example."},{"time":530000,"text":"And this openness is the beginning of exploratory play."},{"time":535000,"text":"Any parents of young kids in the audience? There must be some."},{"time":538000,"text":"Yeah, thought so. So we’ve all seen it, haven’t we?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":541000,"text":"We’ve all told stories about how, on Christmas morning,"},{"time":544000,"text":"our kids end up playing with the boxes"},{"time":546000,"text":"far more than they play with the toys that are inside them."},{"time":549000,"text":"And you know, from an exploration perspective,"},{"time":553000,"text":"this behavior makes complete sense."},{"time":555000,"text":"Because you can do a lot more with boxes than you can do with a toy."},{"time":558000,"text":"Even one like, say, Tickle Me Elmo --"},{"time":561000,"text":"which, despite its ingenuity, really only does one thing,"},{"time":564000,"text":"whereas boxes offer an infinite number of choices."},{"time":571000,"text":"So again, this is another one of those playful activities"},{"time":573000,"text":"that, as we get older, we tend to forget and we have to relearn."}]},{"cues":[{"time":578000,"text":"So another one of Bob McKim’s favorite exercises"},{"time":581000,"text":"is called the \"30 Circles Test.\""},{"time":582000,"text":"So we’re back to work. You guys are going to get back to work again."},{"time":585000,"text":"Turn that piece of paper that you did the sketch on"},{"time":587000,"text":"back over, and you’ll find those 30 circles printed on the piece of paper."},{"time":591000,"text":"So it should look like this. You should be looking at something like this."},{"time":593000,"text":"So what I’m going to do is, I’m going to give you minute,"},{"time":596000,"text":"and I want you to adapt as many of those circles as you can"},{"time":599000,"text":"into objects of some form."},{"time":601000,"text":"So for example, you could turn one into a football,"},{"time":603000,"text":"or another one into a sun. All I’m interested in is quantity."},{"time":606000,"text":"I want you to do as many of them as you can,"},{"time":609000,"text":"in the minute that I’m just about to give you."},{"time":612000,"text":"So, everybody ready? OK? Off you go."}]},{"cues":[{"time":630000,"text":"Okay. Put down your pencils, as they say."},{"time":634000,"text":"So, who got more than five circles figured out?"},{"time":637000,"text":"Hopefully everybody? More than 10?"},{"time":639000,"text":"Keep your hands up if you did 10."},{"time":641000,"text":"15? 20? Anybody get all 30?"},{"time":644000,"text":"No? Oh! Somebody did. Fantastic."},{"time":647000,"text":"Did anybody to a variation on a theme? Like a smiley face?"},{"time":652000,"text":"Happy face? Sad face? Sleepy face? Anybody do that?"},{"time":657000,"text":"Anybody use my examples? The sun and the football?"},{"time":661000,"text":"Great. Cool. So I was really interested in quantity."},{"time":665000,"text":"I wasn’t actually very interested in whether they were all different."},{"time":668000,"text":"I just wanted you to fill in as many circles as possible."},{"time":671000,"text":"And one of the things we tend to do as adults, again, is we edit things."},{"time":676000,"text":"We stop ourselves from doing things."},{"time":677000,"text":"We self-edit as we’re having ideas."}]},{"cues":[{"time":679000,"text":"And in some cases, our desire to be original is actually a form of editing."},{"time":685000,"text":"And that actually isn’t necessarily really playful."},{"time":689000,"text":"So that ability just to go for it and explore lots of things,"},{"time":694000,"text":"even if they don’t seem that different from each other,"},{"time":696000,"text":"is actually something that kids do well, and it is a form of play."},{"time":702000,"text":"So now, Bob McKim did another"},{"time":704000,"text":"version of this test"},{"time":705000,"text":"in a rather famous experiment that was done in the 1960s."},{"time":709000,"text":"Anybody know what this is? It’s the peyote cactus."},{"time":714000,"text":"It’s the plant from which you can create mescaline,"},{"time":716000,"text":"one of the psychedelic drugs."},{"time":718000,"text":"For those of you around in the '60s, you probably know it well."}]},{"cues":[{"time":719000,"text":"McKim published a paper in 1966, describing an experiment"},{"time":725000,"text":"that he and his colleagues conducted"},{"time":726000,"text":"to test the effects of psychedelic drugs on creativity."},{"time":730000,"text":"So he picked 27 professionals -- they were"},{"time":737000,"text":"engineers, physicists, mathematicians, architects,"},{"time":739000,"text":"furniture designers even, artists --"},{"time":742000,"text":"and he asked them to come along one evening,"},{"time":745000,"text":"and to bring a problem with them that they were working on."},{"time":752000,"text":"He gave each of them some mescaline,"},{"time":754000,"text":"and had them listen to some nice, relaxing music for a while."},{"time":758000,"text":"And then he did what’s called the Purdue Creativity Test."},{"time":764000,"text":"You might know it as, \"How many uses can you find for a paper clip?\""},{"time":767000,"text":"It’s basically the same thing as the 30 circles thing that I just had you do."}]},{"cues":[{"time":771000,"text":"Now, actually, he gave the test before the drugs"},{"time":773000,"text":"and after the drugs, to see"},{"time":777000,"text":"what the difference was in people’s"},{"time":779000,"text":"facility and speed with coming up with ideas."},{"time":782000,"text":"And then he asked them to go away"},{"time":783000,"text":"and work on those problems that they’d brought."},{"time":787000,"text":"And they’d come up with a bunch of"},{"time":789000,"text":"interesting solutions -- and actually, quite"},{"time":791000,"text":"valid solutions -- to the things that they’d been working on."},{"time":794000,"text":"And so, some of the things that they figured out,"},{"time":795000,"text":"some of these individuals figured out;"},{"time":797000,"text":"in one case, a new commercial building and designs for houses"},{"time":800000,"text":"that were accepted by clients;"},{"time":801000,"text":"a design of a solar space probe experiment;"},{"time":805000,"text":"a redesign of the linear electron accelerator;"},{"time":810000,"text":"an engineering improvement to a magnetic tape recorder --"},{"time":812000,"text":"you can tell this is a while ago;"},{"time":813000,"text":"the completion of a line of furniture;"},{"time":817000,"text":"and even a new conceptual model of the photon."},{"time":820000,"text":"So it was a pretty successful evening."}]},{"cues":[{"time":822000,"text":"In fact, maybe this experiment was the reason that Silicon Valley"},{"time":826000,"text":"got off to its great start with innovation."},{"time":829000,"text":"We don’t know, but it may be."},{"time":830000,"text":"We need to ask some of the CEOs"},{"time":831000,"text":"whether they were involved in this mescaline experiment."},{"time":833000,"text":"But really, it wasn’t the drugs that were important;"},{"time":837000,"text":"it was this idea that what the drugs did"},{"time":838000,"text":"would help shock people out of their normal way of thinking,"},{"time":841000,"text":"and getting them to forget the adult behaviors"},{"time":845000,"text":"that were getting in the way of their ideas."},{"time":848000,"text":"But it’s hard to break our habits, our adult habits."}]},{"cues":[{"time":852000,"text":"At IDEO we have brainstorming rules written on the walls."},{"time":856000,"text":"Edicts like, \"Defer judgment,\" or \"Go for quantity.\""},{"time":860000,"text":"And somehow that seems wrong."},{"time":861000,"text":"I mean, can you have rules about creativity?"},{"time":863000,"text":"Well, it sort of turns out that we need rules"},{"time":865000,"text":"to help us break the old rules and norms"},{"time":868000,"text":"that otherwise we might bring to the creative process."},{"time":872000,"text":"And we’ve certainly learnt that over time,"},{"time":873000,"text":"you get much better brainstorming,"},{"time":875000,"text":"much more creative outcomes when everybody does play by the rules."},{"time":881000,"text":"Now, of course, many designers, many individual designers,"},{"time":884000,"text":"achieve this is in a much more organic way."}]},{"cues":[{"time":886000,"text":"I think the Eameses are wonderful examples of experimentation."},{"time":891000,"text":"And they experimented with plywood for many years"},{"time":894000,"text":"without necessarily having one single goal in mind."},{"time":897000,"text":"They were exploring following what was interesting to them."},{"time":901000,"text":"They went from designing splints for wounded soldiers"},{"time":903000,"text":"coming out of World War II and the Korean War, I think,"},{"time":906000,"text":"and from this experiment they moved on to chairs."}]},{"cues":[{"time":908000,"text":"Through constant experimentation with materials,"},{"time":910000,"text":"they developed a wide range of iconic solutions"},{"time":913000,"text":"that we know today, eventually resulting in,"},{"time":915000,"text":"of course, the legendary lounge chair."},{"time":917000,"text":"Now, if the Eameses had stopped with that first great solution,"},{"time":920000,"text":"then we wouldn’t be the beneficiaries of so many"},{"time":923000,"text":"wonderful designs today."},{"time":926000,"text":"And of course, they used experimentation in all aspects of their work,"},{"time":930000,"text":"from films to buildings, from games to graphics."},{"time":936000,"text":"So, they’re great examples, I think, of exploration"},{"time":940000,"text":"and experimentation in design."}]},{"cues":[{"time":942000,"text":"Now, while the Eameses were exploring those possibilities,"},{"time":945000,"text":"they were also exploring physical objects."},{"time":948000,"text":"And they were doing that through building prototypes."},{"time":951000,"text":"And building is the next of the behaviors that I thought I’d talk about."},{"time":956000,"text":"So the average Western first-grader"},{"time":958000,"text":"spends as much as 50 percent of their play time"},{"time":961000,"text":"taking part in what’s called \"construction play.\""},{"time":964000,"text":"Construction play -- it’s playful, obviously,"},{"time":967000,"text":"but also a powerful way to learn."},{"time":969000,"text":"When play is about building a tower out of blocks,"},{"time":974000,"text":"the kid begins to learn a lot about towers."},{"time":976000,"text":"And as they repeatedly knock it down and start again,"},{"time":978000,"text":"learning is happening as a sort of by-product of play."},{"time":982000,"text":"It’s classically learning by doing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":986000,"text":"Now, David Kelley calls this behavior,"},{"time":987000,"text":"when it’s carried out by designers, \"thinking with your hands.\""},{"time":991000,"text":"And it typically involves making multiple,"},{"time":994000,"text":"low-resolution prototypes very quickly,"},{"time":997000,"text":"often by bringing lots of found elements together"},{"time":999000,"text":"in order to get to a solution."},{"time":1002000,"text":"On one of his earliest projects, the team was kind of stuck,"},{"time":1006000,"text":"and they came up with a mechanism by hacking together"},{"time":1010000,"text":"a prototype made from a roll-on deodorant."},{"time":1013000,"text":"Now, that became the first commercial computer mouse"},{"time":1015000,"text":"for the Apple Lisa and the Macintosh."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1017000,"text":"So, they learned their way to that by building prototypes."},{"time":1023000,"text":"Another example is a group of designers"},{"time":1025000,"text":"who were working on a surgical instrument with some surgeons."},{"time":1028000,"text":"They were meeting with them; they were talking to the surgeons"},{"time":1030000,"text":"about what it was they needed with this device."},{"time":1033000,"text":"And one of the designers ran out of the room"},{"time":1035000,"text":"and grabbed a white board marker and a film canister --"},{"time":1038000,"text":"which is now becoming a very precious prototyping medium --"},{"time":1041000,"text":"and a clothespin. He taped them all together,"},{"time":1043000,"text":"ran back into the room and said, \"You mean, something like this?\""},{"time":1045000,"text":"And the surgeons grabbed hold of it and said,"},{"time":1047000,"text":"well, I want to hold it like this, or like that."},{"time":1049000,"text":"And all of a sudden a productive conversation"},{"time":1051000,"text":"was happening about design around a tangible object."},{"time":1056000,"text":"And in the end it turned into a real device."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1060000,"text":"And so this behavior is all about quickly getting something"},{"time":1063000,"text":"into the real world, and having your thinking advanced as a result."},{"time":1068000,"text":"At IDEO there’s a kind of a back-to-preschool feel"},{"time":1071000,"text":"sometimes about the environment."},{"time":1073000,"text":"The prototyping carts, filled with colored paper"},{"time":1076000,"text":"and Play-Doh and glue sticks and stuff --"},{"time":1079000,"text":"I mean, they do have a bit of a kindergarten feel to them."},{"time":1082000,"text":"But the important idea is that everything’s at hand, everything’s around."},{"time":1086000,"text":"So when designers are working on ideas,"},{"time":1088000,"text":"they can start building stuff whenever they want."},{"time":1091000,"text":"They don’t necessarily even have to go"},{"time":1092000,"text":"into some kind of formal workshop to do it."},{"time":1094000,"text":"And we think that’s pretty important."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1096000,"text":"And then the sad thing is, although preschools"},{"time":1098000,"text":"are full of this kind of stuff, as kids go through the school system"},{"time":1102000,"text":"it all gets taken away."},{"time":1104000,"text":"They lose this stuff that facilitates"},{"time":1106000,"text":"this sort of playful and building mode of thinking."},{"time":1111000,"text":"And of course, by the time you get to the average workplace,"},{"time":1113000,"text":"maybe the best construction tool we have"},{"time":1116000,"text":"might be the Post-it notes. It’s pretty barren."},{"time":1119000,"text":"But by giving project teams and the clients"},{"time":1123000,"text":"who they’re working with permission to think with their hands,"},{"time":1125000,"text":"quite complex ideas can spring into life"},{"time":1130000,"text":"and go right through to execution much more easily."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1134000,"text":"This is a nurse using a very simple -- as you can see -- plasticine prototype,"},{"time":1138000,"text":"explaining what she wants out of a portable information system"},{"time":1141000,"text":"to a team of technologists and designers"},{"time":1144000,"text":"that are working with her in a hospital."},{"time":1147000,"text":"And just having this very simple prototype"},{"time":1148000,"text":"allows her to talk about what she wants in a much more powerful way."},{"time":1153000,"text":"And of course, by building quick prototypes,"},{"time":1155000,"text":"we can get out and test our ideas with consumers"},{"time":1158000,"text":"and users much more quickly"},{"time":1160000,"text":"than if we’re trying to describe them through words."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1166000,"text":"But what about designing something that isn’t physical?"},{"time":1169000,"text":"Something like a service or an experience?"},{"time":1171000,"text":"Something that exists as a series of interactions over time?"},{"time":1174000,"text":"Instead of building play, this can be approached with role-play."},{"time":1180000,"text":"So, if you’re designing an interaction between two people --"},{"time":1182000,"text":"such as, I don’t know -- ordering food at a fast food joint"},{"time":1185000,"text":"or something, you need to be able to imagine"},{"time":1187000,"text":"how that experience might feel over a period of time."},{"time":1190000,"text":"And I think the best way to achieve that,"},{"time":1192000,"text":"and get a feeling for any flaws in your design, is to act it out."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1197000,"text":"So we do quite a lot of work at IDEO"},{"time":1199000,"text":"trying to convince our clients of this."},{"time":1201000,"text":"They can be a little skeptical; I’ll come back to that."},{"time":1203000,"text":"But a place, I think, where the effort is really worthwhile"},{"time":1207000,"text":"is where people are wrestling with quite serious problems --"},{"time":1211000,"text":"things like education or security or finance or health."},{"time":1216000,"text":"And this is another example in a healthcare environment"},{"time":1219000,"text":"of some doctors and some nurses and designers"},{"time":1221000,"text":"acting out a service scenario around patient care."},{"time":1225000,"text":"But you know, many adults"},{"time":1226000,"text":"are pretty reluctant to engage with role-play."},{"time":1229000,"text":"Some of it’s embarrassment and some of it is because"},{"time":1231000,"text":"they just don’t believe that what emerges is necessarily valid."},{"time":1235000,"text":"They dismiss an interesting interaction by saying,"},{"time":1237000,"text":"you know, \"That’s just happening because they’re acting it out.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":1240000,"text":"Research into kids' behavior actually suggests"},{"time":1242000,"text":"that it’s worth taking role-playing seriously."},{"time":1245000,"text":"Because when children play a role,"},{"time":1246000,"text":"they actually follow social scripts quite closely"},{"time":1249000,"text":"that they’ve learnt from us as adults."},{"time":1251000,"text":"If one kid plays \"store,\" and another one’s playing \"house,\""},{"time":1254000,"text":"then the whole kind of play falls down."},{"time":1257000,"text":"So they get used to quite quickly"},{"time":1260000,"text":"to understanding the rules for social interactions,"},{"time":1264000,"text":"and are actually quite quick to point out when they’re broken."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1267000,"text":"So when, as adults, we role-play,"},{"time":1270000,"text":"then we have a huge set of these scripts already internalized."},{"time":1275000,"text":"We’ve gone through lots of experiences in life,"},{"time":1277000,"text":"and they provide a strong intuition"},{"time":1280000,"text":"as to whether an interaction is going to work."},{"time":1283000,"text":"So we’re very good, when acting out a solution,"},{"time":1285000,"text":"at spotting whether something lacks authenticity."},{"time":1290000,"text":"So role-play is actually, I think,"},{"time":1291000,"text":"quite valuable when it comes to thinking about experiences."},{"time":1295000,"text":"Another way for us, as designers, to explore role-play"},{"time":1298000,"text":"is to put ourselves through an experience which we’re designing for,"},{"time":1302000,"text":"and project ourselves into an experience."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1305000,"text":"So here are some designers who are trying to understand"},{"time":1307000,"text":"what it might feel like to sleep in a"},{"time":1310000,"text":"confined space on an airplane."},{"time":1312000,"text":"And so they grabbed some very simple materials, you can see,"},{"time":1314000,"text":"and did this role-play, this kind of very crude role-play,"},{"time":1318000,"text":"just to get a sense of what it would be like for passengers"},{"time":1320000,"text":"if they were stuck in quite small places on airplanes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1325000,"text":"This is one of our designers, Kristian Simsarian,"},{"time":1327000,"text":"and he’s putting himself through the experience of being an ER patient."},{"time":1331000,"text":"Now, this is a real hospital, in a real emergency room."},{"time":1333000,"text":"One of the reasons he chose to take"},{"time":1335000,"text":"this rather large video camera with him was"},{"time":1336000,"text":"because he didn’t want the doctors and nurses thinking"},{"time":1338000,"text":"he was actually sick, and sticking something into him"},{"time":1341000,"text":"that he was going to regret later."},{"time":1343000,"text":"So anyhow, he went there with his video camera,"},{"time":1346000,"text":"and it’s kind of interesting to see what he brought back."},{"time":1350000,"text":"Because when we looked at the video when he got back,"},{"time":1352000,"text":"we saw 20 minutes of this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1354000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1357000,"text":"And also, the amazing thing about this video --"},{"time":1360000,"text":"as soon as you see it you immediately"},{"time":1362000,"text":"project yourself into that experience."},{"time":1365000,"text":"And you know what it feels like: all of that uncertainty"},{"time":1367000,"text":"while you’re left out in the hallway"},{"time":1369000,"text":"while the docs are dealing with some more urgent case"},{"time":1371000,"text":"in one of the emergency rooms, wondering what the heck’s going on."},{"time":1375000,"text":"And so this notion of using role-play --"},{"time":1377000,"text":"or in this case, living through the experience"},{"time":1380000,"text":"as a way of creating empathy --"},{"time":1381000,"text":"particularly when you use video, is really powerful."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1384000,"text":"Or another one of our designers, Altay Sendil:"},{"time":1386000,"text":"he’s here having his chest waxed, not because he’s very vain,"},{"time":1389000,"text":"although actually he is -- no, I’m kidding --"},{"time":1391000,"text":"but in order to empathize with the pain that chronic care patients"},{"time":1395000,"text":"go through when they’re having dressings removed."},{"time":1397000,"text":"And so sometimes these analogous experiences,"},{"time":1400000,"text":"analogous role-play, can also be quite valuable."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1403000,"text":"So when a kid dresses up as a firefighter, you know,"},{"time":1406000,"text":"he’s beginning to try on that identity."},{"time":1408000,"text":"He wants to know what it feels like to be a firefighter."},{"time":1411000,"text":"We’re doing the same thing as designers."},{"time":1413000,"text":"We’re trying on these experiences."},{"time":1415000,"text":"And so the idea of role-play is both as an empathy tool,"},{"time":1419000,"text":"as well as a tool for prototyping experiences."},{"time":1423000,"text":"And you know, we kind of admire people who do this at IDEO anyway."},{"time":1428000,"text":"Not just because they lead to insights about the experience,"},{"time":1431000,"text":"but also because of their willingness to explore"},{"time":1434000,"text":"and their ability to unselfconsciously"},{"time":1437000,"text":"surrender themselves to the experience."},{"time":1440000,"text":"In short, we admire their willingness to play."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1445000,"text":"Playful exploration, playful building and role-play:"},{"time":1451000,"text":"those are some of the ways that designers use play in their work."},{"time":1454000,"text":"And so far, I admit, this might feel"},{"time":1458000,"text":"like it’s a message just to go out and play like a kid."},{"time":1461000,"text":"And to certain extent it is, but I want to stress a couple of points."},{"time":1465000,"text":"The first thing to remember is that play is not anarchy."},{"time":1468000,"text":"Play has rules, especially when it’s group play."},{"time":1473000,"text":"When kids play tea party, or they play cops and robbers,"},{"time":1477000,"text":"they’re following a script that they’ve agreed to."},{"time":1480000,"text":"And it’s this code negotiation that leads to productive play."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1485000,"text":"So, remember the sketching task we did at the beginning?"},{"time":1487000,"text":"The kind of little face, the portrait you did?"},{"time":1489000,"text":"Well, imagine if you did the same task with friends"},{"time":1493000,"text":"while you were drinking in a pub."},{"time":1495000,"text":"But everybody agreed to play a game"},{"time":1498000,"text":"where the worst sketch artist bought the next round of drinks."},{"time":1502000,"text":"That framework of rules would have turned an embarrassing,"},{"time":1506000,"text":"difficult situation into a fun game."},{"time":1508000,"text":"As a result, we’d all feel perfectly secure and have a good time --"},{"time":1514000,"text":"but because we all understood the rules and we agreed on them together."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1519000,"text":"But there aren’t just rules about how to play;"},{"time":1523000,"text":"there are rules about when to play."},{"time":1526000,"text":"Kids don’t play all the time, obviously."},{"time":1528000,"text":"They transition in and out of it,"},{"time":1530000,"text":"and good teachers spend a lot of time"},{"time":1533000,"text":"thinking about how to move kids through these experiences."},{"time":1537000,"text":"As designers, we need to be able to transition in and out of play also."},{"time":1542000,"text":"And if we’re running design studios"},{"time":1544000,"text":"we need to be able to figure out, how can we transition"},{"time":1546000,"text":"designers through these different experiences?"},{"time":1549000,"text":"I think this is particularly true if we think about the sort of --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1552000,"text":"I think what’s very different about design"},{"time":1555000,"text":"is that we go through these two very distinctive modes of operation."},{"time":1559000,"text":"We go through a sort of generative mode,"},{"time":1564000,"text":"where we’re exploring many ideas;"},{"time":1565000,"text":"and then we come back together again,"},{"time":1567000,"text":"and come back looking for that solution,"},{"time":1570000,"text":"and developing that solution."},{"time":1571000,"text":"I think they’re two quite different modes:"},{"time":1574000,"text":"divergence and convergence."},{"time":1577000,"text":"And I think it’s probably in the divergent mode"},{"time":1580000,"text":"that we most need playfulness."},{"time":1582000,"text":"Perhaps in convergent mode we need to be more serious."},{"time":1585000,"text":"And so being able to move between those modes"},{"time":1587000,"text":"is really quite important. So, it’s where there’s a"},{"time":1591000,"text":"more nuanced version view of play, I think, is required."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1594000,"text":"Because it’s very easy to fall into the trap that these states are absolute."},{"time":1597000,"text":"You’re either playful or you’re serious, and you can’t be both."},{"time":1601000,"text":"But that’s not really true: you can be a serious professional adult"},{"time":1606000,"text":"and, at times, be playful."},{"time":1609000,"text":"It’s not an either/or; it’s an \"and.\""},{"time":1611000,"text":"You can be serious and play."},{"time":1615000,"text":"So to sum it up, we need trust to play,"},{"time":1621000,"text":"and we need trust to be creative. So, there’s a connection."},{"time":1625000,"text":"And there are a series of behaviors that we’ve learnt as kids,"},{"time":1628000,"text":"and that turn out to be quite useful to us as designers."},{"time":1631000,"text":"They include exploration, which is about going for quantity;"},{"time":1636000,"text":"building, and thinking with your hands;"},{"time":1639000,"text":"and role-play, where acting it out helps us both"},{"time":1643000,"text":"to have more empathy for the situations in which we’re designing,"},{"time":1646000,"text":"and to create services and experiences"},{"time":1649000,"text":"that are seamless and authentic."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1653000,"text":"Thank you very much. (Applause)"}]}]}